    <h2>FAQ</h2>

    <h3>What is Siberia and why is it legendary?</h3>
    <p>Siberia is a Swedish ultra-strong nicotine pouch brand made by GN Tobacco. Launched in the mid-2000s, it became a cult phenomenon for extreme-strength users seeking 25+ mg nicotine. The -80°C branding refers to the intense cooling sensation, not temperature. Siberia defined the 'extreme strength' category and remains the benchmark all competitors reference.</p>

    <h3>What does -80°C mean on Siberia?</h3>
    <p>The -80°C branding is marketing shorthand for extreme cooling intensity. It does not mean the pouch is literally at -80 degrees Celsius (which would be impossible). It describes the sensory experience: a powerful minty cooling effect that feels Arctic-intense. The cooling is created through natural mint compounds and pouch formula, not cryogenic freezing.</p>

    <h3>Which Siberia product is the absolute strongest?</h3>
    <p>Siberia Maxi All White at 49.5 mg is the strongest product in the entire range — and one of the strongest nicotine pouches globally. It's a large-format pouch (maxi) with maximum nicotine concentration. Below that: Long Portion (35 mg), Portion (33 mg), Slim (25 mg), and entry-level Ultra Slim (16.5 mg).</p>

    <h3>Is Siberia safe? What should I know about extreme strength?</h3>
    <p>Siberia is safe when used responsibly by experienced users. However, ultra-high nicotine carries risks: nicotine poisoning (tremors, dizziness, vomiting), tolerance buildup, and dependency. Never start Siberia as your first nicotine product. Ensure adequate hydration, monitor for side effects, and discontinue if dizziness or nausea occur. For medical concerns, consult your doctor or visit <a href="https://my.clevelandclinic.org/health/diseases/21582-nicotine-poisoning">Cleveland Clinic: Nicotine Poisoning</a>.</p>

