    <h2>How to Use Siberia Safely: Practical Guidance</h2>

    <h3>If You're New to Siberia (But Experienced with 12+ mg):</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Start with Ultra Slim (16.5 mg). Not Slim (25 mg). Not Portion (33 mg). Ultra Slim.</li>
        <li>Use once. Observe how your body responds over 24 hours. Headache? Dizziness? Nausea? Stop and wait a week.</li>
        <li>If no side effects, wait 3–4 days before using again. Your tolerance needs time to adjust.</li>
        <li>After 2–3 weeks at Ultra Slim, consider Mini (21.5 mg).</li>
        <li>Never jump more than one tier per month. Ever.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Hydration Protocol:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Drink 300–500 ml of water before using Siberia.</li>
        <li>Drink 300 ml more during the pouch session.</li>
        <li>Continue hydrating for 4 hours after removal.</li>
        <li>Dehydration amplifies nicotine poisoning symptoms dramatically.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Spit, Don't Swallow:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Siberia generates significant saliva. Spit it out — do not swallow.</li>
        <li>Swallowing amplifies nicotine absorption; poisoning risk doubles.</li>
        <li>Get a spittoon or use the sink regularly.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Duration and Frequency:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Duration:</strong> 30–60 minutes per pouch (not longer).</li>
        <li><strong>Frequency:</strong> Maximum one pouch every 6 hours. Never concurrent pouches.</li>
        <li><strong>Daily limit:</strong> Until proven, limit to one pouch per day. Tolerance tests require medical supervision.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Final Thoughts: Siberia Isn't For Everyone — And That's OK</h2>

    <p>Siberia is legendary for a reason. It's not a casual nicotine pouch. It's a boundary-pushing experience for users who've earned the tolerance through progressive adaptation. The -80°C cooling, the strength tiers, the cult community — it all culminates in a brand identity that commands respect.</p>

    <p>But Siberia is also a commitment. It's not something you grab casually. It demands respect, hydration, patience, and honest self-assessment of your tolerance. If you're contemplating Siberia, start Ultra Slim, go slow, and listen to your body. The legend will still be there in a month.</p>

